        "created_at": "2020-04-19T16:09:37.160Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I use MX linux (Debian).  these are the installation instructions</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">curl -s https://updates.signal.org/desktop/apt/keys.asc | sudo apt-key add -\n  echo \"deb [arch=amd64] https://updates.signal.org/desktop/apt xenial main\" | sudo tee -a /etc/apt/sources.list.d/signal-xenial.list\n  sudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install signal-desktop\n</code></pre>\n<p>I get to the   sudo apt-key add -   and it just sits there.  I add the next line and it just sits there.  Can someone make this more clear.  Thank you</p>",
