        "avatar_template": "/user_avatar/community.signalusers.org/awaitlink/{size}/48975_2.png",
        "created_at": "2020-04-19T17:20:47.162Z",
        "cooked": "<p>Could you provide the exact commands you’re running, line by line? I suspect you may be running the two commands on the first line separately, which isn’t what the instructions say.</p>\n<p>If you however entered the first line in full, and it is stuck, instead try separating the command and running just the first part, but without <code>-s</code> so it prints some information:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">curl https://updates.signal.org/desktop/apt/keys.asc\n</code></pre>\n<p>This should fetch the file. Since we removed <code>-s</code> it should tell you if it fails and why.</p>\n<p>Another reason it might be “stuck” is because <code>sudo</code> is waiting for you to enter your user’s password.</p>",
