        "created_at": "2025-03-02T10:50:36.709Z",
        "cooked": "<p>I once also stumbled upon this part. It is still today very badly visible to understand that the second bullet point hast to be entered within ONE line, although shown at <a href=\"http://signal.org\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">signal.org</a> in two lines.</p>\n<p>See here:</p>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://ibb.co/q3rTvh85\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/8/6/8612668a93567d5895525f60bf5adc036d7812a6.png\" class=\"site-icon\" data-dominant-color=\"5EBFE8\" width=\"300\" height=\"300\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://ibb.co/q3rTvh85\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">ImgBB</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <img width=\"180\" height=\"180\" src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/3X/7/1/71931e7aff608386f9d684464704f1ccb398ec87.png\" class=\"thumbnail onebox-avatar\" data-dominant-color=\"CACACA\">\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://ibb.co/q3rTvh85\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\">Bildschirmfoto-vom-2025-03-02-11-42-00 hosted at ImgBB</a></h3>\n\n  <p>Image Bildschirmfoto-vom-2025-03-02-11-42-00 hosted in ImgBB</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n\n<p>And the first bullet point are two separate commands…? Or not? I even don’t remember. They are also shown in two lines.</p>\n<p>By the way, still today, the source contains the word “xenial”, which is a reference to Ubuntu Xenial Xerus, whose support ended 2021-04-30. Compare Ubuntu Version history in wikipedia. Weird.</p>\n<p>I guess, at least the layout should be very easily fixable, with the additional remark: “Enter the following command within one line”</p>\n<p>Or did I miss something?</p>",
