    "name": "link ✦",
    "excerpt": "<p>Okay so that’s going fine separately. Note that in the 1st and 2nd lines, the second command relies on the output of the previous one (via <code>|</code>). You can’t run them separately and expect it to just work (you’d need to know some more shell basics for that, to adjust them).</p>\n<p>So you should do it like this instead:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>Enter or copy and paste <strong>this whole line</strong> then press <kbd>Enter</kbd>:</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">curl -s https://updates.signal.org/desktop/apt/keys.asc | sudo apt-key add -\n</code></pre>\n<ol start=\"2\">\n<li>\n<p>Enter your user password if prompted.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Then same with this:</p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">echo \"deb [arch=amd64] https://updates.signal.org/desktop/apt xenial main\" | sudo tee -a /etc/apt/sources.list.d/signal-xenial.list\n</code></pre>\n<ol start=\"4\">\n<li>And finally:</li>\n</ol>\n<pre><code class=\"lang-auto\">sudo apt update &amp;&amp; sudo apt install signal-desktop\n</code></pre>\n<ol start=\"5\">\n<li>Now you should be able to find Signal in the usual place where you launch applications from.</li>\n<li>Then follow the steps here to link your Signal Desktop to your primary device:</li>\n</ol>\n<aside class=\"onebox allowlistedgeneric\" data-onebox-src=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/360007320551-Linked-Devices#link_desktop\">\n  <header class=\"source\">\n      <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/2X/3/396bf78ae2909b3ca1dc0e597dad5606f0eae8bd.png\" class=\"site-icon\" width=\"32\" height=\"32\">\n\n      <a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/360007320551-Linked-Devices#link_desktop\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Signal Support</a>\n  </header>\n\n  <article class=\"onebox-body\">\n    <img src=\"https://community.signalusers.org/uploads/db3609/original/2X/0/0218b2e17a3861d99954e99ac27ae1084f4a1295.png\" class=\"thumbnail onebox-avatar\" width=\"156\" height=\"156\">\n\n<h3><a href=\"https://support.signal.org/hc/en-us/articles/360007320551-Linked-Devices#link_desktop\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Linked Devices</a></h3>\n\n  <p>You can link Signal Desktop or Signal iPad to your phone. All Signal communication on linked devices are private.\nNote:\n\nYour previous message history is not synchronized. Only new chats sent or re...</p>\n\n\n  </article>\n\n  <div class=\"onebox-metadata\">\n    \n    \n  </div>\n\n  <div style=\"clear: both\"></div>\n</aside>\n"
  },
